headlines.description: — Kemba Walker tied a season high with 32 points in his return from a four-game injury absence, Evan Fournier had 18 points in his first game back in Orlando since being traded, and the Boston Celtics routed the Magic 132-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker returns from injury, scores 32  as Celtics whip Magic

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 32 points and nine assists and Enes Kanter had 18 points and 13 rebounds, leading the Portland Trail Blazers to their highest point total of the season and a 141-105 rout of the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lilliard scores 32, Trail Blazers rout Cavaliers 141-105

headlines.description: — Clint Capela scored 18 points to lead seven scorers in double figures and the Atlanta Hawks pulled away late to overcome Devin Booker's 30 points and rout the Phoenix Suns 135-103 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Capela, Hawks pull away late to take 135-103 win over Suns

headlines.description: — Marvin Bagley III kept Sacramento's slim playoff hopes alive Wednesday night with a breakthrough game by scoring a season-high 31 points and grabbing 12 rebounds to lead the the Kings past the Indiana Pacers 104-93.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bagley's fast start helps Kings race past Pacers 104-93

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 34 points in just 25 minutes and the Philadelphia 76ers extended their winning streak to six games with a 135-115 victory over the short-handed Houston Rockets on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid has 34 points in 3 quarters, 76ers beat Rockets

headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday scored 29 points and the Milwaukee Bucks withstood a triple-double from Russell Westbrook and edged the Washington Wizards 135-134 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks edge Wizards 135-134 to earn fourth straight victory

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 37 points and 10 assists and the Memphis Grizzlies held on for a 139-135 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Grizzlies hold on for 138-132 win over Wolves

events.name: New York Knicks at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 24 of his 32 points in a dominant first quarter in the Denver Nuggets' 113-97 victory over the New York Knicks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic, Nuggets start fast, cool off Knicks

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored 30 points, Bojan Bogdanovic added 24 and the Utah Jazz routed the San Antonio Spurs 126-94 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Clarkson scores 30 points, Jazz rout Spurs 126-94
